      • getTable

        DataTableModel getTable(java.lang.String tableName)
                 throws CalLiteGUIException
        This method will take the Table Name and return the DataTableModle object of that table.
        Parameters:
        tableName - Name of the table with the option like D1641 or D1485.
        Returns:
        It will return the table as DataTableModel.
        Throws:
        CalLiteGUIException - When loading the tables if it gets an error it will throw it.

      • getTable

        DataTableModel getTable(java.lang.String tableName,
                        ThreeFunction<java.util.List<java.lang.String>,java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String,java.lang.String[][]> function)
                 throws CalLiteGUIException
        This method will take the Table Name and the function that gets the data and return the DataTableModle object of that table.
        Parameters:
        tableName - Just the table name without the path and extension.
        function - The function which retrieve the data from the table file.
        Returns:
        The DataTableModel object with whole table.
        Throws:
        CalLiteGUIException - If anything wrong about the file then it will throw a exception with the information about it.
